query:
INSERT INTO protocolChunks (countyId, protocolNumber, protocolTitle, section, content)
SELECT id, 'R-001', 'Asthma/COPD/Bronchospasm Protocol', 'Respiratory',
'ASTHMA/COPD/BRONCHOSPASM PROTOCOL

ASSESSMENT: History of asthma/COPD. Wheezing, prolonged expiratory phase. Accessory muscle use, tripod positioning.

SEVERITY: Mild - speaks in sentences, SpO2 >94%. Moderate - speaks in phrases, SpO2 90-94%, accessory muscle use. Severe - speaks in words only, SpO2 <90%, cyanosis.

TREATMENT:
1. OXYGEN - Titrate to SpO2 >94% (88-92% for known CO2 retainers).

2. BRONCHODILATORS - Albuterol 2.5mg nebulized, may repeat every 5-10 minutes x3. Ipratropium (Atrovent) 0.5mg nebulized, may combine with albuterol (DuoNeb).

3. CORTICOSTEROIDS - Methylprednisolone 125mg IV or Prednisone 60mg PO if able.

4. SEVERE/IMPENDING RESPIRATORY FAILURE - Epinephrine 0.3mg IM (1:1000). Magnesium Sulfate 2g IV over 20 minutes.

5. CPAP - For moderate-severe distress. Start at 5 cmH2O, increase to 10-15 as tolerated. Contraindicated if unable to protect airway.

6. IF RESPIRATORY FAILURE - Prepare for intubation. BVM with PEEP valve.

PEDIATRIC DOSING: Albuterol 2.5mg if <20kg, 5mg if >20kg. Epinephrine 0.01mg/kg IM (max 0.3mg).'
FROM counties;
